Description: Glazed steatite scaraboid with relief decoration on the back in the form of two back-to-back rams' heads wearing the solar-disc with Wedjat-eyes inbetween, feathered legs, longitudinally pierced, the base inscribed with the nomen of Shabako flanked by uraei and decorated with a representation of a sejant sphinx and a flying vulture.
Curator's comments: Published: Andrews, Amulets of Ancient Egypt (1994): p.54
